# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ZHA frontend — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev. In Vercel, add these under
# Project Settings → Environment Variables (Production + Preview).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase — REQUIRED (the only variables read at runtime).
# From Supabase → Project Settings → API.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# Service-role key — ADMIN/LOCAL ONLY. Used by one-off migration/admin scripts,
# never by the app at runtime. DO NOT add this to Vercel.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# YouTube cookie — needed ONLY for audio playback when hosted on a datacenter IP
# (e.g. Vercel). YouTube blocks streaming from cloud IPs ("Sign in to confirm
# you're not a bot"); an authenticated cookie bypasses it. Not needed for local
# dev (a home/residential IP isn't blocked). Server-only secret (NOT public).
#
# How to get it: sign in to youtube.com in a browser → DevTools → Network → pick
# any request to youtube.com → copy the full `cookie:` request header value.
# Paste the whole string here / into the Vercel env var. It expires periodically
# and must be refreshed. Using a personal account for this is against YouTube ToS.
# YOUTUBE_COOKIE=VISITOR_INFO1_LIVE=...; __Secure-3PSID=...; __Secure-3PAPISID=...; ...
